Serializable
public class RelationSet

Utility class for managing a set of GATE relations (usually each annotation set of a document will have one set of associated relations).

indexesByMember

protected List<Map<Integer,BitSet>> indexesByMember
Indexes for relations by member. Each element in the list refers to a given position in the members array: the element at position zero refers to the first member of all relations. The element at position pos is a map from annotation ID (representing a relation member) to a BitSet indicating which of the relation indexes (in relations) correspond to relations that contain the given annotation (i.e. member) on the position pos.

Method Detail

getRelations

public static RelationSet getRelations(Document document,
                                       String name)
Factory method that gets a named RelationSet from a document. RelationSets are stored inside a special document feature, which is where this method retrieves them from. If no relation set is associated with the given name, then a new one is created and returned. To get the relation set associated with a given annotation set use getRelations(AnnotationSet) instead.

Parameters:
document - the document for which the relations are being requested.
name - the name for the relation set. This can be any arbitrary String or even null. However, by convention, names of annotation sets (and null for the default annotation set) are used to name the principal relation set for each annotation set.
Returns:
the RelationSet requested.
